OL,6,FMrs Justice May said: "The applicant
OL,7,Fappears to have a settled, perverse
OL,8,Fsexual interest in young girls. He has
OL,9,Fminimised the harm caused to his
OL,10,Fvictims.
OL,12,F"In these circumstances, we can
OL,13,Funderstand the judge's conclusion that
OL,14,Fit was impossible to conclude when or
OL,15,Fif the risk posed by the applicant
OL,16,Fwould cease.
OL,18,F"We are not persuaded that the
OL,19,Fapplicant should be differently
OL,20,Fsentenced. The sentence thus remains
OL,21,Fin all respects as it was before."
