OL,3,CPaedophile former police officer loses
OL,4,Cappeal against life sentence
OL,6,FSusan Ferrier, for Edwards, said:
OL,7,F"Life imprisonment should always be a
OL,8,Fsentence of last resort, this being a
OL,9,Fyoung man who at the time of the
OL,10,Foffending which he pleaded guilty to
OL,11,Fwas identified as somebody who,
OL,12,Falthough he had gained entry into the
OL,13,Fpolice force, was somebody who was not
OL,14,Fjust a young man but someone who was
OL,15,Femotionally immature."
OL,17,FRoger Griffiths, representing the
OL,18,FCrown Prosecution Service, said: "The
OL,19,Fsentence is not one that is manifestly
OL,20,Fexcessive in the circumstances of this
OL,21,Fcase."
